The yields of toxic products for the two non-flaming materials GW and SW are shown in Table 7. It is not correct to relate this data to an equivalence ratio since flaming did not occur, but the materials were tested under the most severe conditions of well-ventilated flaming using temperatures of 825°C or 850°C rather than 650°C, as directed in ISO TS 19700 to try to obtain flaming combustion.

